Their middle order has struggled in this series and West Indies would be relying heavily on Brian Lara, Shivnarine Chanderpaul, Chris Gayle and Ramnaresh Sarwan to see them through.

The Australians are out on the field taking their positions. Brett Lee is just going through his paces ahead of taking the new ball. Gayle and Chanderpaul are out in the middle.

That's it from me, Sriram Veera. Jamie Alter will pick up the chase.

**********************************************

Hello and welcome to Cricinfo's live coverage of the DLF Cup. This is Binoy George, and I'll be taking you through the action as it unfolds at the Kinrara Academy Oval at Malaysia.

We've witnessed some intense cricket in the league matches, and it all now comes down to this game - the Grand Final. World Champions Australia take on the West Indies in this Winner-takes-all game.

Australia, edged India out of the title clash in the last league match on the 22nd September, while West Indies booked their spot earlier in the tournament.

There's been a contest within a contest in almost every match in this tournament, and in this match, its again going to be the clash of the two titans - Glenn McGrath Vs Brian Lara. McGrath has been as good as ever, keeping the ball in the right areas and forcing the batsmen to make mistakes - who could tell from his performance here that he had had a prolonged absence from international cricket.

Lara, on the other hand, has shown glimpses of his good form, and the West Indies will be hoping that Lara carries his good form into this title clash, and further into the ICC Champions Trophy that will be played in a fortnight's time.

The weather forecast doesn't look all that promising for this all important game - the met department has predicted spells of rain through the day.

Pitch report: The pitch for today's match is the same pitch that had been used for 4 other matches earlier in the tournament; there is some wear and tear and it is expected to play slow. The team winning the toss would surely like to bat first.

It is the time for the toss, Ricky Ponting flips the coin in the air, tails called by Lara, it comes down as head, Ponting opts to bat.

Toss: Australia have won the toss and elected to bat.

Teams: The Australian team for the final Katich, Watson, Ponting, Clarke, Symonds, Hussey, Martyn, Haddin, Lee, Bracken and McGrath. For West Indies Gayle, Chanderpaul, Sarwan, Lara, Bravo, Smith, Hinds, Morton, Carlton Baugh, Taylor and Bradshaw.

Ponting had hinted at the toss that Shane Watson would be coming up the order. Please stay tuned, intense contest on the cards, join us in a few minutes when the action starts.
